## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="01772-242">Quando un <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> scrive il testo nel proprio flusso di errore standard, che è in genere visualizzato nella console.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-242">When a <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> writes text to its standard error stream, that text is typically displayed on the console.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-243">Reindirizzando il <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> flusso, è possibile modificare o eliminare l'output di errore di un processo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-243">By redirecting the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream, you can manipulate or suppress the error output of a process.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-244">Ad esempio, è possibile filtrare il testo, formattarlo in modo diverso o scrivere l'output sia nella console e un determinato file di log.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-244">For example, you can filter the text, format it differently, or write the output to both the console and a designated log file.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="01772-245">È necessario impostare <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.UseShellExecute%2A> a `false` se si desidera impostare <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.RedirectStandardError%2A> a `true`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-245">You must set <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.UseShellExecute%2A> to `false` if you want to set <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.RedirectStandardError%2A> to `true`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-246">In caso contrario, leggere la <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> flusso genera un'eccezione.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-246">Otherwise, reading from the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream throws an exception.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="01772-247">Reindirizzato <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> flusso può essere letto in modo sincrono o asincrono.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-247">The redirected <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream can be read synchronously or asynchronously.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-248">I metodi come <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.Read%2A>, <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A> e <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadToEnd%2A> eseguire le operazioni di lettura sincrona nel flusso di output di errore del processo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-248">Methods such as <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.Read%2A>, <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A> and <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadToEnd%2A> perform synchronous read operations on the error output stream of the process.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-249">Questi sincrono letti operazioni non vengono completate fino a quando l'oggetto associato <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> scrive relativo <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream o chiude il flusso.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-249">These synchronous read operations do not complete until the associated <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> writes to its <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream, or closes the stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="01772-250">Al contrario, <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginErrorReadLine%2A> operazioni di lettura asincrona viene avviato nel <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> flusso.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-250">In contrast, <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginErrorReadLine%2A> starts asynchronous read operations on the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-251">Questo metodo consente a un gestore eventi designato per l'output del flusso e restituisce immediatamente al chiamante, che è possibile eseguire altro lavoro mentre l'output di flusso viene indirizzato al gestore dell'evento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-251">This method enables a designated event handler for the stream output and immediately returns to the caller, which can perform other work while the stream output is directed to the event handler.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="01772-252">L'applicazione di elaborazione dell'output asincrono deve chiamare il <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.WaitForExit%2A> metodo per assicurarsi che il buffer di output è stato scaricato.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-252">The application that is processing the asynchronous output should call the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.WaitForExit%2A> method to ensure that the output buffer has been flushed.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="01772-253">Operazioni introducono una dipendenza tra la lettura dal chiamante di lettura sincrona di <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> flusso e il processo figlio scrive in tale flusso.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-253">Synchronous read operations introduce a dependency between the caller reading from the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream and the child process writing to that stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-254">Queste dipendenze possono causare condizioni di deadlock.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-254">These dependencies can cause deadlock conditions.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-255">Quando il chiamante legge dal flusso reindirizzato di un processo figlio, è dipendente dal figlio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-255">When the caller reads from the redirected stream of a child process, it is dependent on the child.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-256">Il chiamante attende che l'operazione di lettura fino a quando l'elemento figlio scrive nel flusso o chiude il flusso.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-256">The caller waits for the read operation until the child writes to the stream or closes the stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-257">Quando il processo figlio scrive dati sufficienti per riempire il relativo flusso reindirizzato, è dipende dal padre.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-257">When the child process writes enough data to fill its redirected stream, it is dependent on the parent.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-258">Il processo figlio attende la successiva operazione di scrittura fino a quando l'elemento padre legge dal flusso completo o chiude il flusso.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-258">The child process waits for the next write operation until the parent reads from the full stream or closes the stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-259">La condizione di deadlock si verifica quando il chiamante e il processo figlio attendere che l'altro per completare un'operazione e non può continuare.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-259">The deadlock condition results when the caller and child process wait for each other to complete an operation, and neither can continue.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-260">Per evitare deadlock, è possibile valutare le dipendenze tra il chiamante e il processo figlio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-260">You can avoid deadlocks by evaluating dependencies between the caller and child process.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="01772-261">Ad esempio, il codice c# seguente viene illustrato come leggere da un flusso reindirizzato e attendere l'uscita del processo figlio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-261">For example, the following C# code shows how to read from a redirected stream and wait for the child process to exit.</span></span>  
  
```  
// Start the child process.  
 Process p = new Process();  
 // Redirect the error stream of the child process.  
 p.StartInfo.UseShellExecute = false;  
 p.StartInfo.RedirectStandardError = true;  
 p.StartInfo.FileName = "Write500Lines.exe";  
 p.Start();  
 // Do not wait for the child process to exit before  
 // reading to the end of its redirected error stream.  
 // p.WaitForExit();  
 // Read the error stream first and then wait.  
 string error = p.StandardError.ReadToEnd();  
 p.WaitForExit();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="01772-262">L'esempio di codice consente di evitare una condizione di deadlock chiamando `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` prima `p.WaitForExit`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-262">The code example avoids a deadlock condition by calling `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` before `p.WaitForExit`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-263">Una condizione di deadlock può verificarsi se il processo padre chiama `p.WaitForExit` prima `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` e il processo figlio scrive testo sufficiente per riempire il flusso reindirizzato.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-263">A deadlock condition can result if the parent process calls `p.WaitForExit` before `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` and the child process writes enough text to fill the redirected stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-264">Il processo padre rimarrebbe indefinitamente in attesa per l'uscita del processo figlio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-264">The parent process would wait indefinitely for the child process to exit.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-265">Il processo figlio rimarrebbe indefinitamente in attesa per l'elemento padre da cui leggere la versione completa <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> flusso.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-265">The child process would wait indefinitely for the parent to read from the full <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="01772-266">Si verifica un problema simile durante la lettura di tutto il testo di output standard e flussi di errore standard.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-266">There is a similar issue when you read all text from both the standard output and standard error streams.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-267">Ad esempio, il codice c# seguente esegue un'operazione di lettura su entrambi i flussi.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-267">For example, the following C# code performs a read operation on both streams.</span></span>  
  
```  
// Do not perform a synchronous read to the end of both  
// redirected streams.  
// string output = p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd();  
// string error = p.StandardError.ReadToEnd();  
// p.WaitForExit();  
// Use asynchronous read operations on at least one of the streams.  
p.BeginOutputReadLine();  
string error = p.StandardError.ReadToEnd();  
p.WaitForExit();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="01772-268">L'esempio di codice consente di evitare la condizione di deadlock mediante l'esecuzione asincrona di operazioni di lettura di <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flusso.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-268">The code example avoids the deadlock condition by performing asynchronous read operations on the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-269">Risultati di una condizione di deadlock se il processo padre chiama `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` seguito da `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` e il processo figlio scrive testo sufficiente per riempire il relativo flusso di errore.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-269">A deadlock condition results if the parent process calls `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` followed by `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` and the child process writes enough text to fill its error stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-270">Il processo padre rimarrebbe indefinitamente in attesa per il processo figlio chiudere la <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> flusso.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-270">The parent process would wait indefinitely for the child process to close its <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-271">Il processo figlio rimarrebbe indefinitamente in attesa per l'elemento padre da cui leggere la versione completa <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> flusso.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-271">The child process would wait indefinitely for the parent to read from the full <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="01772-272">Per evitare queste dipendenze e i potenziali deadlock, è possibile utilizzare le operazioni di lettura asincrone.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-272">You can use asynchronous read operations to avoid these dependencies and their deadlock potential.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="01772-273">In alternativa, è possibile evitare la condizione di deadlock creando due thread e leggendo l'output di ogni flusso in un thread separato.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="01772-273">Alternately, you can avoid the deadlock condition by creating two threads and reading the output of each stream on a separate thread.</span></span>  
  
   
  
